&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mandya.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Union Ministers Dr. Mansukh Mandaviya and Shri H.D. Kumaraswamy laid the foundation stone for a ₹14-crore indoor sports complex in Mandya, Karnataka.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; The complex is being built within the campus of the &lt;strong&gt;University of Agricultural Sciences (VC Farm)&lt;/strong&gt; in Mandya.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scheme:&lt;/strong&gt; The project is sanctioned under the &lt;strong&gt;Khelo India Scheme&lt;/strong&gt; to promote grassroots sports.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vision:&lt;/strong&gt; The initiative is driven by the slogan &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Khelo India! Vibrant Mandya!&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; to produce national-level champions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CSR Support:&lt;/strong&gt; Alongside the sports project, &lt;strong&gt;388 Persons with Disabilities&lt;/strong&gt; received electric vehicles through CSR initiatives of TCS and SAIL.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Social Welfare:&lt;/strong&gt; The event also saw Infosys donating 600 computers to schools and the Hinduja Group providing an ambulance to MIMS Mandya.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Khelo India Scheme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A flagship national program launched by the Ministry of Youth Affairs and Sports to revive the sports culture in India at the grassroots level.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Mandya Geography&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Mandya is often called the &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Sugar City&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; (Sakkare Nadu) of Karnataka due to its extensive sugarcane cultivation and sugar factories.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Umri.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Union Minister Shri Jyotiraditya M. Scindia inaugurated the Samriddhi Kendra at Umri Village in Madhya Pradesh under the Samriddhi Gram Phygital Services Initiative.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Phygital Model:&lt;/strong&gt; The centre combines &lt;strong&gt;Physical infrastructure with Digital services&lt;/strong&gt; to provide single-window access to healthcare, education, and finance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infrastructure:&lt;/strong&gt; It leverages the high-speed broadband connectivity provided under the &lt;strong&gt;BharatNet&lt;/strong&gt; project.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Health Services:&lt;/strong&gt; Includes &lt;strong&gt;Telemedicine&lt;/strong&gt;, Health ATMs for diagnostics, and affordable medicines through Janaushadhi Pariyojana.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agri-Tech:&lt;/strong&gt; Provides modern farming solutions like &lt;strong&gt;Soil Testing&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Drone-based services&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Connectivity:&lt;/strong&gt; Features public Wi-Fi access under the &lt;strong&gt;PM-WANI&lt;/strong&gt; framework and digital banking facilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Phygital&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A portmanteau of &amp;quot;Physical&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Digital,&amp;quot; referring to the integration of digital experiences with physical ones.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;PM-WANI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Prime Minister&amp;rsquo;s Wi-Fi Access Network Interface aims to increase wireless internet hotspots across the country to boost digital connectivity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To safeguard lawyers from violence and harassment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Government of Goa has approved the Goa Advocate Protection Bill 2026 during a cabinet meeting to ensure the security of legal professionals.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Legal Safeguards:&lt;/strong&gt; The bill protects advocates from &lt;strong&gt;Violence, Harassment, and Wrongful Accusations&lt;/strong&gt; occurring while they perform their professional duties.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strict Penalties:&lt;/strong&gt; It proposes rigorous legal action against individuals who &lt;strong&gt;attack or threaten&lt;/strong&gt; lawyers in connection with their work.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preventing False Implication:&lt;/strong&gt; A core focus is to stop the &lt;strong&gt;false implication&lt;/strong&gt; of advocates during the discharge of their legal responsibilities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working Environment:&lt;/strong&gt; The legislation aims to create a &lt;strong&gt;fear-free environment&lt;/strong&gt;, ensuring that external pressure or physical harm does not hinder the justice system.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Security Focus:&lt;/strong&gt; By introducing these provisions, the state government intends to strengthen the &lt;strong&gt;safety and security&lt;/strong&gt; of all members of the legal profession.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Rajasthan Precedent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In 2023, &lt;strong&gt;Rajasthan&lt;/strong&gt; became the first state in India to pass a specific Advocate Protection Act. Goa&amp;#39;s move aligns with a growing national demand from Bar Councils for similar protections.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Bar Council of India (BCI)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The BCI is a statutory body that regulates legal practice and education in India, which has been advocating for a Central-level Advocate Protection Act.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First crewed lunar flyby.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA)&amp;nbsp;targeted April 1, 2026, for the launch of Artemis II, the first crewed mission to the Moon since the Apollo era.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mission Nature:&lt;/strong&gt; Artemis II is a &lt;strong&gt;10-day crewed lunar flyby&lt;/strong&gt; mission; it will not land on the Moon but will travel around its far side.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Crew:&lt;/strong&gt; The mission features four astronauts: &lt;strong&gt;Reid Wiseman, Victor Glover, Christina Koch (USA), and Jeremy Hansen (Canada)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Launch System:&lt;/strong&gt; The spacecraft will be launched using the &lt;strong&gt;Space Launch System (SLS)&lt;/strong&gt; rocket from Kennedy Space Center, Florida.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Hurdles:&lt;/strong&gt; The April launch date follows several delays caused by &lt;strong&gt;helium leaks and fuel system issues&lt;/strong&gt; discovered during testing.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Program Roadmap:&lt;/strong&gt; While Artemis II is a flyby, &lt;strong&gt;Artemis IV&lt;/strong&gt; is currently intended to facilitate the program&amp;#39;s first crewed lunar landing in 2028.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Orion Spacecraft&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The capsule designed to carry the crew. It is built to withstand the high-speed, high-heat reentry into Earth&amp;#39;s atmosphere from lunar distances.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Diversity in Artemis&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Artemis II will include the first woman (Christina Koch), the first person of color (Victor Glover), and the first non-American (Jeremy Hansen) to travel to the vicinity of the Moon.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prof. Yashwant Gupta.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prof. Yashwant Gupta was conferred with the MP Birla Memorial Award 2025 at a ceremony held at the MP Birla Planetarium on 13th March.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Designation:&lt;/strong&gt; Prof. Gupta is the Distinguished Professor and Centre Director at the &lt;strong&gt;National Centre for Radio Astrophysics (NCRA-TIFR)&lt;/strong&gt;, Pune.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Contribution:&lt;/strong&gt; He was recognized for his pioneering research in &lt;strong&gt;Radio Astronomy&lt;/strong&gt; and his leadership in national scientific initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Award:&lt;/strong&gt; Instituted in 1993, this biennial award honors excellence in &lt;strong&gt;Astronomy, Astrophysics, and Space Sciences&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ceremony Highlights:&lt;/strong&gt; The award includes a citation, trophy, cash prize, and a memorial lecture delivered by the recipient.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Significance:&lt;/strong&gt; The MP Birla Planetarium presents this honor to eminent Indian scientists who have made world-class contributions to space science.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;NCRA-TIFR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The National Centre for Radio Astrophysics is located in Pune and operates the &lt;strong&gt;Giant Metrewave Radio Telescope (GMRT)&lt;/strong&gt;, one of the world&amp;#39;s largest radio telescopes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Radio Astronomy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A subfield of astronomy that studies celestial objects at radio frequencies, allowing scientists to observe phenomena invisible to optical telescopes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
